The paper deals with privacy-preserving data outsourcing and distributed data processing, which are common topics in computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), and data structures (cs.DS). The use of MapReduce as an underlying programming model also suggests a potential fit for the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
